originalText.text:
Really loved the energy here!
We arrived at 8:00am and it took 20 minutes to get us through.
We waited in the seating area and had access to lockers to drop our stuff.
The staff are helpful and tried best to coordinate things.
Tamron was a darling. She is very cute and charismatic. I enjoyed being in the audience and got a gift.

Loved my visit to the Tamron Hall Show. She has such great energy and comes across so genuine!
One negative unrelated to the show was that the bathrooms had no soap and it was mentioned that they had been out since the day prior.

originalText.text:
Super fun experience! However, we showed up at 8:30am with our priority tickets, which was just too early and wasn’t necessary. Too much time sitting and waiting in a room that only had a cut-out of Tamron that you could take a photo with and TVs playing old shows. No coffee or water offered for sale, either, so make sure you grab coffee before arriving.

Other than spending too much time twiddling our thumbs, our experience was lovely!!

originalText.text:
I’ve been to the Tamron show on 3 occasions. And if they keep inviting me I’ll continue to go! They have lockers to hold your items in the colder months and wifi invade you are an out of towner.

This latest show included a Tasting Table with different individuals: Bun B (Activist/Artist/Business Owner: Trill Burger), Joey (internet food critic), Jadakiss & fam (Business Owner: Kiss Cafe/Rapper), etc. It was a long taping than usually but Tamron was very informative & apologetic. We had fun—danced a bit & received swag (stickers/rubber cuffs). There was a group of Flight Attendants that also attended & gave good information (ie you can tip them via candy, face mask/beauty related items, gift cards or monetary ).

Word to the wise their entrance/line is up the street from The Views area/line.
